India]] and [[Panchayati raj (India)]].\n<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.censusindia.gov.in/pca/SearchDetails.aspx?Id=26040| title= Maniala| work=census2011.co.in | accessdate=5 August 2016}}</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n<!-- Please Note: Do not add any promotional\n information on this page. Any promotional/spam\n Links or any other information added will be\n removed immediately -->\n\n==List of cities near the village== \n*[[Bhulath]]\n*[[Kapurthala]] \n*[[Phagwara]] \n*[[Sultanpur Lodhi]]\n\n==Air travel connectivity== \nThe closest International airport to the village is [[Sri Guru Ram Dass Jee International Airport]].\n\n==External links==\n* [https://www.censusindia.gov.in/2011census/Listofvillagesandtowns.aspx Villages in Kapurthala]\n* [https://villageinfo.in/punjab/kapurthala/kapurthala.html List of Villages in Kapurthala Tehsil]\n\n{{Kapurthala district |state=collapsed}}\n\n[[Category:Villages in Kapurthala district]]\n\n\n{{PunjabIN-geo-stub}}\n", "name_user": "SDZeroBot", "label": "safe", "comment": "Stub sorting: replacing PunjabIN-geo-stub with Kapurthala-geo-stub", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Maniala"}
{"title_page": "Emilio Kauderer", "text_new": "{{short description|Argentine musician}}{{Infobox musical artist\n| background       = non_vocal_instrumentalist\n| occupation       = [[Composer]], [[Conducting|conductor]], orchestrator, [[songwriter]]\n| associated_acts  = [[Bajofondo]], [[Gustavo Santaolalla]], [[Juan Campodonico]], [[Luis Avalos]]\n| birth_place      = Argentina\n| instrument       = Piano\n}}\n\n'''Emilio Kauderer''' is an [[Argentina|Argentine]] [[composer]], orchestrator and [[songwriter]] residing in [[Los Angeles]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.paginasiete.bo/cultura/2018/11/25/la-banda-sonora-es-obra-del-argentino-emilio-kauderer-201217.html|title=La banda sonora es obra del argentino Emilio Kauderer - Diario Pagina Siete|website=www.paginasiete.bo|language=es|access-date=2020-04-13}}</ref> He is best known for his scores for films including \"[[Underdogs (2013 Argentine film)|Metegol (Underdogs)]]\", \"[[Secret in Their Eyes]]\", and \"[[A Place in the World (film)|A Place In the World]]\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://milanrecords.com/soundtracks/the-secret-in-their-eyes/|title=The Secret In Their Eyes - original music by Emilio Kauderer & Federico Jusid|website=Milan Records|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-13}}</ref><ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.latimes.com/entertainment/arts/la-et-cm-dudamel-blades-bowl-review-20140731-column.html|title=Review: Ruben Blades, Gustavo Dudamel can't quite connect with Bowl|date=2014-07-30|website=Los Angeles Times|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-13}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.latimes.com/archives/la-xpm-2001-jan-26-me-17396-story.html|title=Knowing the Score|date=2001-01-26|website=Los Angeles Times|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-13}}</ref> Kauderer won a [[Latin Grammy Award|Latin Grammy]] for his work on [[Bajofondo|Bajofondo's]] 2002 album \"[[Bajofondo Tango Club (album)|Bajofondo Tango Club]]\".<ref name=\":1\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.latingrammy.com/es/nominees/search?artist=&field_nominee_work_value=&year=2003&genre=All|title=20a Entrega Anual del Latin GRAMMY|website=Latin GRAMMYs|language=es|access-date=2020-04-13}}</ref>\n\n==Early life and education==\nKauderer was born in Argentina. He studied composition with [[Jacobo Ficher]], and conducting with Jaques Bodmer. He performed as a classical pianist and trained at the [[Petro Tchaikovsky National Music Academy of Ukraine|Tchaikovsky Conservatory in Kiev]] in piano playing, music composition and conducting with Sagaidachni and Kanershtein. Kauderer continued studies at Gnesina College of Music in Moscow and obtained a postgraduate degree at the [[Moscow Conservatory|Tchaikovsky Moscow Conservatory]] on a full merit scholarship with Naumov.<ref name=\":2\">{{Cite web|url=https://nettv4u.com/celebrity/english/music-composer/emilio-kauderer|title=Hollywood Music Composer Emilio Kauderer Biography, News, Photos, Videos|website=nettv4u|language=en|access-date=2020-04-13}}</ref>\n\n== Career ==\n\n=== Works in Argentina ===\nUpon his return to Argentina, his chamber compositions were performed by the [[Camerata Bariloche]]. Keuderer's Wind Quintet \"Danz\u00f3n\" won the Yamaha-Promusica Award in 1987.<ref name=\":2\" /> He began work in [[Cinema of Argentina|Argentinian movies]] in 1980, composing for the film ''[[La Discoteca del amor]]'', which was directed by [[Adolfo Aristarain]].<ref>{{Citation|last=SensaCine|title=Reparto de La discoteca del amor : Equipo T\u00e9cnico, Producci\u00f3n y Distribuci\u00f3n|url=http://www.sensacine.com/peliculas/pelicula-189209/reparto/|access-date=2020-04-13}}</ref>\n\n=== Orchestral work ===\nHe received a fellowship to The [[Sundance Institute|Sundance Institute's]] Composer's Lab and was honored by being selected as the composer of the music for New York's Jewish Heritage Museum main exhibit piece.<ref name=\":4\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.ficg.mx/catalogo29/appfiles/assets/basic-html/page47.html|title=Festival Internacional de Cine en Guadalajara -Cat\u00e1logo de Pel\u00edculas {{!}} FICG29|website=www.ficg.mx|access-date=2020-04-13}}</ref> The musical Paquito's Christmas, written with Luis Avalos, was performed and conducted by Kauderer at the Washington Opera. The musical featured [[Pl\u00e1cido Domingo|Pl\u00e1cido Domingo's]] grandson for three seasons and played at the Pasadena Civic Center in Los Angeles for nine years. Kauderer's symphonic work has been performed by the National Symphonic Orchestras in Argentina,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://newwestsymphony.org/happy-250th-ludwig/eroica-trio/|title=Eroica Trio|website=New West Symphony|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-13}}</ref> Honduras, the La Porte Symphony Orchestra and the Pan American Symphony Orchestra in Washington.<ref name=\":2\" /><ref name=\":3\">{{Cite book|last=|first=|url=https://calperformances.org/learn/program_notes/2010/pn_tba.pdf|title=Cal Performances 2010-2011|publisher=|year=|isbn=|location=|pages=}}</ref>\n\nKauderer's orchestral work was performed by the [[Los Angeles Philharmonic]] at the [[Hollywood Bowl]] conducted by [[Gustavo Dudamel]].<ref name=\":0\" /><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.broadwayworld.com/los-angeles/article/Additional-Programming-Announced-for-NOCHE-DE-CINE-with-Gustavo-Dudamel-731-20140627|title=Additional Programming Announced for NOCHE DE CINE with Gustavo Dudamel, 7/31|last=Desk|first=BWW News|website=BroadwayWorld.com|language=en|access-date=2020-04-13}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.motionpictures.org/2016/02/world-renown-composer-emilio-kauderer-scoring-animation-underdogs/|title=World Renown Composer Emilio Kauderer on Scoring Animation in Underdogs {{!}} The Credits|last=Wasley|first=Alice|date=2016-02-03|website=Motion Picture Association|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-13}}</ref> Other orchestral work has been performed by the Washington Opera, the London Symphony Orchestra, the London Philharmonia Orchestra, the Prague Philharmonic, the Pan American Orchestra in Washington and the National Symphony Orchestras of both Argentina and Honduras.<ref name=\":2\" /><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://kyivdiplomatic.com/en/news/174|title=Embassy of Argentina in Ukraine invites composer Emilio Kauderer to award ceremony|website=kyivdiplomatic.com|access-date=2020-04-13}}</ref>\n\nKauderer composed the music for the 60th anniversary of the Holiday on Ice show, Diamonds which was warmly received by European audiences for four years. He collaborated with Michael Kamen for the opening of the Winter Olympics, wrote the AT&T song for Jon Secada's performance at the Olympic Games in Seoul and wrote the music for Ricky Martin's videos for the [[Livin' la Vida Loca]] tour in collaboration with KC Porter.<ref name=\":3\" /><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://moviescoremedia.com/border-run-emilio-kauderer-sebastian-kauderer/|title=Border Run (Emilio Kauderer & Sebasti\u00e1n Kauderer)|website=moviescoremedia.com|access-date=2020-04-13}}</ref>\n\n=== Film scoring ===\nIn 2019, Kauderer became the first music composer to win the Molodist Award (Lifetime Achievement, Odessa Film Festival). (Past recipients include but are not limited to Roman Polanski, Catherine Deneuve, Sophia Lauren and Claudia Cardinale.) Kauderer was honored with the Arbol de La Vida Award by the 2013 Guadalajara International Film Festival in Los Angeles (FICG in LA).<ref>{{Cite book|last=|first=|url=https://www.ficg.mx/la/highlights2014/appfiles/assets/common/downloads/Highlights-FICGinLA-2013.pdf|title=Highlights of the 2013 FICG in LA|publisher=|year=2013|isbn=|location=|pages=}}</ref> The Los Angeles County Board of Supervisors granted Kauderer recognition for his outstanding contribution to film music. Kauderer was the recipient of a fellowship to The Sundance Institute's Composers Lab and the BMI Conductors Lab.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bmi.com/news/entry/20011201_2001_sundance_composers_lab|title=2001 Sundance Composers Lab|date=2001-11-30|website=BMI.com|language=en|access-date=2020-04-13}}</ref> He was honored by having been selected as the composer of the music for the main exhibit piece of New York's Jewish History Museum.<ref name=\":3\" />\n\nKauderer composed the score for the remake of [[Secret in Their Eyes]], directed by Billy Ray, and the 3D animated film [[Underdogs (2013 animated film)|Metegol/Futbolin/Underdogs]], directed by [[Juan Campanella]];<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ellitoral.com/index.php/id_um/99408-metegol-gana-dos-premios-platino-de-cine|title=\"Metegol\" gana dos Premios Platino de cine|website=www.ellitoral.com|access-date=2020-04-13}}</ref> Corazon de Leon, directed by Marcos Carnevale; and [[Amapola (film)|Amapola]], directed by [[Eugenio Zanetti]]. Kauderer collaborated with director Juan Campanella on the soundtracks of [[Same Love, Same Rain]], [[Vientos de Agua]], El Hombre de tu Vida, [[The Secret in Their Eyes]], co-composed with Federico Jusid, [[Belgrano (film)|Belgrano]] and [[Parque Lezama]].<ref name=\":3\" /> In collaboration with director [[Adolfo Aristarain]], Kaudererwrote the music score for [[A Place in the World (film)|A Place in the World]], [[Time for Revenge]], [[\u00daltimos d\u00edas de la v\u00edctima (film)|\u00daltimos d\u00edas de la v\u00edctima]] and [[La Discoteca del Amor]].<ref name=\":3\" /> To date, Kauderer has won three Academy Awards in Argentina for Best Film Score for the films: \"Metegol/Underdogs,\" Secret in Their Eyes, and A Place In the World. Secret in Their Eyes won the [[Academy Awards|Academy Award]] for Best Foreign Language Film in [[82nd Academy Awards|2010]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.oscars.org/oscars/ceremonies/2010|title=The 82nd Academy Awards {{!}} 2010|website=Oscars.org {{!}} Academy of Motion Picture Arts and Sciences|language=en|access-date=2020-04-13}}</ref>\n\n=== TV work ===\nRecent music credits for TV include the FOX series '[[2091 (TV series)|2091]]', Familia en Venta and [[Cumbia Ninja]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.tvmasmagazine.com/en/2016/04/10/english-inician-en-colombia-el-rodaje-de-la-serie-2091/|title=In Colombia started the filming of the series 2091|last=TVMAS|date=2016-04-10|website=TVMAS Magazine|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-13}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.sadaic.org.ar/obras.autor.php?paginate=4&codigo=264721|title=obras.form|website=www.sadaic.org.ar|access-date=2020-04-13}}</ref> Kauderer collaborated with [[Stewart Copeland]] on the theme and music for the Emmy-nominated score of the Showtime series, [[Dead Like Me]].<ref name=\":4\" />\n\n===Video game work===\nEmilio Kauderer collaborated with [[Stewart Copeland]] in composing a song for the ''Stomp'' album and the soundtrack for the ''[[Spyro (series)|Spyro]]'' series of games on [[Sony]]'s [[PlayStation 2]].<ref name=\"Nominaciones\">{{Cite web|url=https://academiadecine.org.ar/premio-sur/premio-sur-2009/nominaciones/|title=Nominaciones|date=2014-10-02|website=Academia de Cine|language=es|access-date=2020-04-13}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.last.fm/music/Emilio+Kauderer/+wiki|title=Emilio Kauderer biography|website=Last.fm|language=en|access-date=2020-04-13}}</ref>\n\n=== [[Bajofondo]] ===\nKauderer participated in [[Bajofondo|Bajofondo's]] [[Latin Grammy Award|Latin Grammy]] winning album [[Bajofondo Tango Club]] with his song \"Maroma\", produced by [[Gustavo Santaolalla]] and [[Juan Campodonico]].<ref name=\":1\" /> The album was critically acclaimed in Argentina and sold well there and in record stores in Los Angeles. [[Universal Music Latin Entertainment|Universal Latino]] then released the album in the United States.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.latimes.com/archives/la-xpm-2003-dec-28-ca-lechner28-story.html|title=Now you can really dance to it|date=2003-12-28|website=Los Angeles Times|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-13}}</ref>\n\n==Awards and nominations==\n\n[[Image:2002 Winter Olympics flame.jpg|thumb|right|250px| [[2002 Winter Olympics]]]]\n\n* 2019 Molodist Award [Lifetime Achievement]; first time Molodist given to music composer.\n* 2019 Premio Sur Nomination for Best Score, composed in collaboration with Alejandro Kauderer for \"My Masterpiece\".\n* 2014 Premio Platino (Panama) for Best Score for \"Metegol\".\n* 2014 Condor de Plata (Nominated) for Best Score for \"Metegol\".\n* 2013 [[Premio Sur]] (Academy Award in Argentina) for Best Score for \"Metegol\".\n* 2013 Arbol de la Vida Award, a recognition by the Guadalajara International Film Festival in Los Angeles (FICG in LA).\n* 2011 Clarin Nomination for Best Soundtrack, \"El Hombre de tu Vida\"\n* 2010 Honored by the President of Argentina to conduct his film music with the National Symphony Orchestra at the closing of the Bicentennial of Argentina's Independence. The event took place in front of 1,5 million people.\n* 2009 Clarin Award for Best Soundtrack (Argentina) \"The Secret in their Eyes.\"\n* 2009 Premio Sur for Best Soundtrack 2009 (Argentina), \"The Secret in their Eyes.\"\n* 2009 Condor de Plata Award 2010 for Best Soundtrack (Argentina), \"The Secret in their Eyes.\"\n* 2009 Nominated to the Goya Awards 2010 for Best Soundtrack (Spain), \"The Secret in their Eyes.\"\n* 2009 Festival Internacional del Nuevo Cine Latinoamericano for Best Soundtrack, \"Miss Bala.\"\n* 2009 Nominated for best soundtrack at the Goya Awards (Spain) \"The Secret in their Eyes.\"\n* 2008 Martin Fierro for Best Soundtrack, \"Vientos de Agua.\"\n* 2007 Clarin Award for Best Soundtrack, \"Vientos de Agua.\"\n* 2006 Kauderer was granted recognition by the Board of Supervisors of the County of Los Angeles.\n* 2005 BMI fellowship to the Conductor's Lab.\n* 2004 Emmy nomination for Best Score, composed in collaboration with Stewart Copeland. \"Dead Like Me\".\n*2003 Latin Grammy for his contribution to \"Bajo Fondo Tango Club,\" produced by Gustavo Santaolalla and Juan Campodonico.\n* 2003 Selected to compose the music for [[New York City]]'s Museum of Tolerance main exhibit piece.\n* 2002 Collaborated with Michael Kamen doing the music of the Opening for the 2002 Winter Olympics\n* 2001 Sundance Institute fellowship to the Composer's Lab.\n* 2001 \"Paquito's Christmas,\" written with Luis Avalos, appears at the Washington Opera and the Pasadena Civic Center, sponsored by Pl\u00e1cido Domingo.\n* 2000 Silver Condor (Critics Award in Argentina) for Best Soundtrack \"El Mismo Amor, La Misma Lluvia\".\n* 1993 [[Premio Sur]] (Academy Award in Argentina) for Best Soundtrack \"A Place in the World\".\n* 1993 Silver Condor (Critics Award in Argentina) for Best Soundtrack \"A Place in the World\".\n\n<ref name=\":1\" /><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://filmmusicreporter.com/2014/04/07/ibero-american-film-industry-launches-platino-awards/|title=Ibero-American Film Industry Launches Platino Awards {{!}} Film Music Reporter|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-13}}</ref><ref name=\":3\" /><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://academiadecine.org.ar/premio-sur-2013/nominaciones/|title=Nominaciones|date=2014-06-01|website=Academia de Cine|language=es|access-date=2020-04-13}}</ref><ref name=\"Nominaciones\"/>\n\n==Filmography==\n*''Como Cortar a Tu Patan'' (2017) \u2013 Composer\n*''Numb, at the Edge of the End'' (2017) \u2013 Composer\n*''Day of Reckoning'' (2016) \u2013 Composer\n*''[[2091 (TV series)|2091]]'' (2016) \u2013 Composer\n*''[[Cumbia Ninja]]'' (2016) \u2013 Composer\n*''El Alien'' (2016) \u2013 Composer\n*''[[Secret in Their Eyes]]'' (2015) \u2013 Composer\n*''[[Underdogs (2013 animated film)|Underdogs]]'' (2015) \u2013 Composer\n*''Alice in Marialand'' (2014) \u2013 Composer\n*''Corazon de Leon'' (2013) \u2013 Composer\n*''[[Amapola (film)|Amapola]]'' (2013) \u2013 Composer \n*''[[Metegol]]'' (2013) \u2013 Composer \n*''Esclavo de Dios'' (2012) \u2013 Composer\n*''[[Border Run]]'' (2013) \u2013 Composer with Sebastian Kauderer\n*''[[Miss Bala (2011 film)|Miss Bala]]'' (2011) \u2013 Composer\n*''El Hombre de tu Vida'' (2011) \u2013 in collaboration with Alejandro Kauderer\n*''[[Love Equation]]'' (2010) \u2013 Composer \n*''[[El secreto de sus ojos]]'' (2009) \u2013 in collaboration with ''[[Federico Jusid]]''\n*''Verano amargo'' (2007) (in production)\n*''[[Vientos de agua]]'' (13 episodes, 2006)\n*''Adios momo'' (2006)\n*''3:52'' (2005)\n*''2+2=5=1'' (2004)\n*''[[Dead Like Me]]'' (7 episodes, 2003\u20132004)\n*\"Te amar\u00e9 en silencio\" (2003) TV Series\n*''[[Indigo (film)|Indigo]]'' (2003)\n*Patriotas, Los (2002)\n*Trysting (2001)\n*''Quantum Project'' (2000)\n*''[[El Mismo Amor, la Misma Lluvia]]'' (1999)\n*Friends & Lovers (1999)\n*Erasable You (1998)\n*''[[Asesinato a distancia]]'' (1998)\n*''[[Women: Stories of Passion]]'' (2 episodes, 1997)\n*''Playback'' (1996)\n*''Hot Line'' (1 episode, 1994)\n*''Tirano Banderas'' (1993)\n*The Ice Runner'' (1993)\n*''Midnight Kiss'' (1993)\n*''[[Al Filo de la Ley (1992 film)|Al filo de la ley]]'' (1992)\n*''[[Un lugar en el mundo]]'' (1992)\n*''[[Gypsy Eyes]]'' (1992)\n*''[[Prototype (1992 film)|Prototype]]'' (1992)\n*''[[Julia Has Two Lovers]]'' (1991)\n*''Crack Me Up'' (1991)\n*''[[Palenque]]'' (1990)\n*''15 Ugly Sisters'' (1990)\n*''Fistfighter'' (1989)\n*''Slash Dance'' (1989)\n*''[[They Call Me Macho Woman!]]'' (1989)\n*''In Dangerous Company'' (1988)\n*''[[Abierto de 18 a 24]]'' (1988)\n*''[[Made in Argentina]]'' (1987)\n*''[[En busca del brillante perdido]]'' (1986)\n*''Bajo tierra'' (1985)\n*''[[Los Fierecillos indomables]]'' (1982)\n*''[[Plata dulce]]'' (1982)\n*''[[\u00daltimos d\u00edas de la v\u00edctima (film)|\u00daltimos d\u00edas de la v\u00edctima]]'' (1982)\n*''[[Tiempo de revancha]]'' (1981)\n*''Las Vacaciones del amor'' (1981)\n*''[[La Discoteca del amor]]'' (1980)\n\n<ref>{{Cite news|last=Seitz|first=Matt Zoller|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2007/04/19/movies/20momo.html|title=Misadventures of a Paper Boy|date=2007-04-19|work=The New York Times|access-date=2020-04-13|language=en-US|issn=0362-4331}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|last=Holden|first=Stephen|url=https://www.nytimes.com/1989/05/12/movies/reviews-film-fistfighter-barehanded-vengeance.html|title=Reviews/Film; 'Fistfighter,' Barehanded Vengeance|date=1989-05-12|work=The New York Times|access-date=2020-04-13|language=en-US|issn=0362-4331}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://archive.nytimes.com/www.nytimes.com/library/film/041699friends-film-review.html|title='Friends and Lovers': On a Weekend Ski Trip, Where It's Very Warm in the Lodge|website=archive.nytimes.com|access-date=2020-04-13}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://catalog.afi.com/Person/261453-Emilio-Kauderer?sid=f29a08c5-124d-4e46-b112-52ee7da71fbd&sr=12.426936&cp=1&pos=0&isMiscCredit=false|title=AFI{{!}}Catalog|website=catalog.afi.com|access-date=2020-04-13}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.moviemusicmania.com/2/post/2014/06/border-run-sebastian-kauderer-and-emilio-kauderer.html|title=Border Run - Sebastian Kauderer and Emilio Kauderer|website=Classic and ModerN Film Score Reviews!|language=en|access-date=2020-04-13}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/review/corazon-de-leon-heart-a-719801|title=\u2018Corazon de Leon\u2019 (\u2018Heart of a Lion\u2019): Film Review|website=The Hollywood Reporter|language=en|access-date=2020-04-13}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/review/miss-bala-cannes-review-188437|title=Miss Bala: Cannes Review|website=The Hollywood Reporter|language=en|access-date=2020-04-13}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-film-missbala-idUSTRE74F02520110516|title=Model Sigman debuts in tense arthouse drug drama \"Miss Bala\"|date=2011-05-16|work=Reuters|access-date=2020-04-13|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://variety.com/2005/film/reviews/goodbye-momo-1200520073/|title=Goodbye Momo|last=Koehler|first=Robert|last2=Koehler|first2=Robert|date=2005-11-24|website=Variety|language=en|access-date=2020-04-13}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{IMDb name|0441985|Emilio Kauderer}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Kauderer, Emilio}}\n[[Category:Argentine film score composers]]\n[[Category:Male film score composers]]\n[[Category:Argentine composers]]\n[[Category:Argentine musicians]]\n[[Category:Year of birth missing (living people)]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Argentine musician}}{{Infobox musical artist\n| background       = non_vocal_instrumentalist\n| occupation       = [[Composer]], [[Conducting|conductor]], orchestrator, [[songwriter]]\n| associated_acts  = [[Bajofondo]], [[Gustavo Santaolalla]], [[Juan Campodonico]], [[Luis Avalos]]\n| birth_place      = Argentina\n| instrument       = Piano\n}}\n\n'''Emilio Kauderer''' is an [[Argentina|Argentine]] [[composer]], orchestrator and [[songwriter]] residing in [[Los Angeles]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.paginasiete.bo/cultura/2018/11/25/la-banda-sonora-es-obra-del-argentino-emilio-kauderer-201217.html|title=La banda sonora es obra del argentino Emilio Kauderer - Diario Pagina Siete|website=www.paginasiete.bo|language=es|access-date=2020-04-13}}</ref> He is best known for his scores for films including \"[[Underdogs (2013 Argentine film)|Metegol (Underdogs)]]\", \"[[Secret in Their Eyes]]\", and \"[[A Place in the World (film)|A Place In the World]]\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://milanrecords.com/soundtracks/the-secret-in-their-eyes/|title=The Secret In Their Eyes - original music by Emilio Kauderer & Federico Jusid|website=Milan Records|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-13}}</ref><ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.latimes.com/entertainment/arts/la-et-cm-dudamel-blades-bowl-review-20140731-column.html|title=Review: Ruben Blades, Gustavo Dudamel can't quite connect with Bowl|date=2014-07-30|website=Los Angeles Times|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-13}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.latimes.com/archives/la-xpm-2001-jan-26-me-17396-story.html|title=Knowing the Score|date=2001-01-26|website=Los Angeles Times|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-13}}</ref> Kauderer won a [[Latin Grammy Award|Latin Grammy]] for his work on [[Bajofondo|Bajofondo's]] 2002 album \"[[Bajofondo Tango Club (album)|Bajofondo Tango Club]]\".<ref name=\":1\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.latingrammy.com/es/nominees/search?artist=&field_nominee_work_value=&year=2003&genre=All|title=20a Entrega Anual del Latin GRAMMY|website=Latin GRAMMYs|language=es|access-date=2020-04-13}}</ref> \n\n==Early life and education==\nKauderer was born in Argentina. He studied composition with [[Jacobo Ficher]], and conducting with Jaques Bodmer. He performed as a classical pianist and trained at the [[Petro Tchaikovsky National Music Academy of Ukraine|Tchaikovsky Conservatory in Kiev]] in piano playing, music composition and conducting with Sagaidachni and Kanershtein. Kauderer continued studies at Gnesina College of Music in Moscow and obtained a postgraduate degree at the [[Moscow Conservatory|Tchaikovsky Moscow Conservatory]] on a full merit scholarship with Naumov.<ref name=\":2\">{{Cite web|url=https://nettv4u.com/celebrity/english/music-composer/emilio-kauderer|title=Hollywood Music Composer Emilio Kauderer Biography, News, Photos, Videos|website=nettv4u|language=en|access-date=2020-04-13}}</ref>\n\n== Career ==\n\n=== Works in Argentina ===\nUpon his return to Argentina, his chamber compositions were performed by the [[Camerata Bariloche]]. Keuderer's Wind Quintet \"Danz\u00f3n\" won the Yamaha-Promusica Award in 1987.<ref name=\":2\" /> He began work in [[Cinema of Argentina|Argentinian movies]] in 1980, composing for the film ''[[La Discoteca del amor]]'', which was directed by [[Adolfo Aristarain]].<ref>{{Citation|last=SensaCine|title=Reparto de La discoteca del amor : Equipo T\u00e9cnico, Producci\u00f3n y Distribuci\u00f3n|url=http://www.sensacine.com/peliculas/pelicula-189209/reparto/|access-date=2020-04-13}}</ref>\n\n=== Orchestral work ===\nHe received a fellowship to The [[Sundance Institute|Sundance Institute's]] Composer's Lab and was honored by being selected as the composer of the music for New York's Jewish Heritage Museum main exhibit piece.<ref name=\":4\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.ficg.mx/catalogo29/appfiles/assets/basic-html/page47.html|title=Festival Internacional de Cine en Guadalajara -Cat\u00e1logo de Pel\u00edculas {{!}} FICG29|website=www.ficg.mx|access-date=2020-04-13}}</ref> The musical Paquito's Christmas, written with Luis Avalos, was performed and conducted by Kauderer at the Washington Opera. The musical featured [[Pl\u00e1cido Domingo|Pl\u00e1cido Domingo's]] grandson for three seasons and played at the Pasadena Civic Center in Los Angeles for nine years. Kauderer's symphonic work has been performed by the National Symphonic Orchestras in Argentina<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://newwestsymphony.org/happy-250th-ludwig/eroica-trio/|title=Eroica Trio|website=New West Symphony|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-13}}</ref>, Honduras, the La Porte Symphony Orchestra and the Pan American Symphony Orchestra in Washington.<ref name=\":2\" /><ref name=\":3\">{{Cite book|last=|first=|url=https://calperformances.org/learn/program_notes/2010/pn_tba.pdf|title=Cal Performances 2010-2011|publisher=|year=|isbn=|location=|pages=}}</ref>\n\nKauderer's orchestral work was performed by the [[Los Angeles Philharmonic]] at the [[Hollywood Bowl]] conducted by [[Gustavo Dudamel|Gustavo Dudamel.]]<ref name=\":0\" /><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.broadwayworld.com/los-angeles/article/Additional-Programming-Announced-for-NOCHE-DE-CINE-with-Gustavo-Dudamel-731-20140627|title=Additional Programming Announced for NOCHE DE CINE with Gustavo Dudamel, 7/31|last=Desk|first=BWW News|website=BroadwayWorld.com|language=en|access-date=2020-04-13}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.motionpictures.org/2016/02/world-renown-composer-emilio-kauderer-scoring-animation-underdogs/|title=World Renown Composer Emilio Kauderer on Scoring Animation in Underdogs {{!}} The Credits|last=Wasley|first=Alice|date=2016-02-03|website=Motion Picture Association|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-13}}</ref> Other orchestral work has been performed by the Washington Opera, the London Symphony Orchestra, the London Philharmonia Orchestra, the Prague Philharmonic, the Pan American Orchestra in Washington and the National Symphony Orchestras of both Argentina and Honduras.<ref name=\":2\" /><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://kyivdiplomatic.com/en/news/174|title=Embassy of Argentina in Ukraine invites composer Emilio Kauderer to award ceremony|website=kyivdiplomatic.com|access-date=2020-04-13}}</ref>\n\nKauderer composed the music for the 60th anniversary of the Holiday on Ice show, Diamonds which was warmly received by European audiences for four years. He collaborated with Michael Kamen for the opening of the Winter Olympics, wrote the AT&T song for Jon Secada's performance at the Olympic Games in Seoul and wrote the music for Ricky Martin's videos for the [[Livin' la Vida Loca]] tour in collaboration with KC Porter.<ref name=\":3\" /><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://moviescoremedia.com/border-run-emilio-kauderer-sebastian-kauderer/|title=Border Run (Emilio Kauderer & Sebasti\u00e1n Kauderer)|website=moviescoremedia.com|access-date=2020-04-13}}</ref>\n\n=== Film scoring ===\nIn 2019, Kauderer became the first music composer to win the Molodist Award (Lifetime Achievement, Odessa Film Festival). (Past recipients include but are not limited to Roman Polanski, Catherine Deneuve, Sophia Lauren and Claudia Cardinale.) Kauderer was honored with the Arbol de La Vida Award by the 2013 Guadalajara International Film Festival in Los Angeles (FICG in LA).<ref>{{Cite book|last=|first=|url=https://www.ficg.mx/la/highlights2014/appfiles/assets/common/downloads/Highlights-FICGinLA-2013.pdf|title=Highlights of the 2013 FICG in LA|publisher=|year=2013|isbn=|location=|pages=}}</ref> The Los Angeles County Board of Supervisors granted Kauderer recognition for his outstanding contribution to film music. Kauderer was the recipient of a fellowship to The Sundance Institute's Composers Lab and the BMI Conductors Lab.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bmi.com/news/entry/20011201_2001_sundance_composers_lab|title=2001 Sundance Composers Lab|date=2001-11-30|website=BMI.com|language=en|access-date=2020-04-13}}</ref> He was honored by having been selected as the composer of the music for the main exhibit piece of New York's Jewish History Museum.<ref name=\":3\" />\n\nKauderer composed the score for the remake of [[Secret in Their Eyes]], directed by Billy Ray, and the 3D animated film [[Underdogs (2013 animated film)|Metegol/Futbolin/Underdogs]], directed by [[Juan Campanella]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ellitoral.com/index.php/id_um/99408-metegol-gana-dos-premios-platino-de-cine|title=\"Metegol\" gana dos Premios Platino de cine|website=www.ellitoral.com|access-date=2020-04-13}}</ref>; Corazon de Leon, directed by Marcos Carnevale; and [[Amapola (film)|Amapola]], directed by [[Eugenio Zanetti]]. Kauderer collaborated with director Juan Campanella on the soundtracks of [[Same Love, Same Rain]], [[Vientos de Agua]], El Hombre de tu Vida, [[The Secret in Their Eyes]], co-composed with Federico Jusid, [[Belgrano (film)|Belgrano]] and [[Parque Lezama]].<ref name=\":3\" /> In collaboration with director [[Adolfo Aristarain]], Kaudererwrote the music score for [[A Place in the World (film)|A Place in the World]], [[Time for Revenge]], [[\u00daltimos d\u00edas de la v\u00edctima (film)|\u00daltimos d\u00edas de la v\u00edctima]] and [[La Discoteca del Amor]].<ref name=\":3\" /> To date, Kauderer has won three Academy Awards in Argentina for Best Film Score for the films: \"Metegol/Underdogs,\" Secret in Their Eyes, and A Place In the World. Secret in Their Eyes won the [[Academy Awards|Academy Award]] for Best Foreign Language Film in [[82nd Academy Awards|2010]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.oscars.org/oscars/ceremonies/2010|title=The 82nd Academy Awards {{!}} 2010|website=Oscars.org {{!}} Academy of Motion Picture Arts and Sciences|language=en|access-date=2020-04-13}}</ref>\n\n=== TV work ===\nRecent music credits for TV include the FOX series '[[2091 (TV series)|2091]]', Familia en Venta and [[Cumbia Ninja]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.tvmasmagazine.com/en/2016/04/10/english-inician-en-colombia-el-rodaje-de-la-serie-2091/|title=In Colombia started the filming of the series 2091|last=TVMAS|date=2016-04-10|website=TVMAS Magazine|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-13}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.sadaic.org.ar/obras.autor.php?paginate=4&codigo=264721|title=obras.form|website=www.sadaic.org.ar|access-date=2020-04-13}}</ref> Kauderer collaborated with [[Stewart Copeland]] on the theme and music for the Emmy-nominated score of the Showtime series, [[Dead Like Me]].<ref name=\":4\" />\n\n===Video game work===\nEmilio Kauderer collaborated with [[Stewart Copeland]] in composing a song for the ''Stomp'' album and the soundtrack for the ''[[Spyro (series)|Spyro]]'' series of games on [[Sony]]'s [[PlayStation 2]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://academiadecine.org.ar/premio-sur/premio-sur-2009/nominaciones/|title=Nominaciones|date=2014-10-02|website=Academia de Cine|language=es|access-date=2020-04-13}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.last.fm/music/Emilio+Kauderer/+wiki|title=Emilio Kauderer biography|website=Last.fm|language=en|access-date=2020-04-13}}</ref>\n\n=== [[Bajofondo]] ===\nKauderer participated in [[Bajofondo|Bajofondo's]] [[Latin Grammy Award|Latin Grammy]] winning album [[Bajofondo Tango Club]] with his song \"Maroma\", produced by [[Gustavo Santaolalla]] and [[Juan Campodonico]].<ref name=\":1\" /> The album was critically acclaimed in Argentina and sold well there and in record stores in Los Angeles. [[Universal Music Latin Entertainment|Universal Latino]] then released the album in the United States.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.latimes.com/archives/la-xpm-2003-dec-28-ca-lechner28-story.html|title=Now you can really dance to it|date=2003-12-28|website=Los Angeles Times|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-13}}</ref>\n\n==Awards and nominations==\n\n[[Image:2002 Winter Olympics flame.jpg|thumb|right|250px| [[2002 Winter Olympics]]]]\n\n* 2019 Molodist Award [Lifetime Achievement]; first time Molodist given to music composer.\n* 2019 Premio Sur Nomination for Best Score, composed in collaboration with Alejandro Kauderer for \"My Masterpiece\".\n* 2014 Premio Platino (Panama) for Best Score for \"Metegol\".\n* 2014 Condor de Plata (Nominated) for Best Score for \"Metegol\".\n* 2013 [[Premio Sur]] (Academy Award in Argentina) for Best Score for \"Metegol\".\n* 2013 Arbol de la Vida Award, a recognition by the Guadalajara International Film Festival in Los Angeles (FICG in LA).\n* 2011 Clarin Nomination for Best Soundtrack, \"El Hombre de tu Vida\"\n* 2010 Honored by the President of Argentina to conduct his film music with the National Symphony Orchestra at the closing of the Bicentennial of Argentina's Independence. The event took place in front of 1,5 million people.\n\n* 2009 Clarin Award for Best Soundtrack (Argentina) \"The Secret in their Eyes.\"\n* 2009 Premio Sur for Best Soundtrack 2009 (Argentina), \"The Secret in their Eyes.\"\n* 2009 Condor de Plata Award 2010 for Best Soundtrack (Argentina), \"The Secret in their Eyes.\"\n* 2009 Nominated to the Goya Awards 2010 for Best Soundtrack (Spain), \"The Secret in their Eyes.\"\n* 2009 Festival Internacional del Nuevo Cine Latinoamericano for Best Soundtrack, \"Miss Bala.\"\n* 2009 Nominated for best soundtrack at the Goya Awards (Spain) \"The Secret in their Eyes.\"\n* 2008 Martin Fierro for Best Soundtrack, \"Vientos de Agua.\"\n* 2007 Clarin Award for Best Soundtrack, \"Vientos de Agua.\"\n* 2006 Kauderer was granted recognition by the Board of Supervisors of the County of Los Angeles.\n* 2005 BMI fellowship to the Conductor's Lab.\n* 2004 Emmy nomination for Best Score, composed in collaboration with Stewart Copeland. \"Dead Like Me\".\n*2003 Latin Grammy for his contribution to \"Bajo Fondo Tango Club,\" produced by Gustavo Santaolalla and Juan Campodonico.\n* 2003 Selected to compose the music for [[New York City]]'s Museum of Tolerance main exhibit piece.\n* 2002 Collaborated with Michael Kamen doing the music of the Opening for the 2002 Winter Olympics\n* 2001 Sundance Institute fellowship to the Composer's Lab.\n* 2001 \"Paquito's Christmas,\" written with Luis Avalos, appears at the Washington Opera and the Pasadena Civic Center, sponsored by Pl\u00e1cido Domingo.\n* 2000 Silver Condor (Critics Award in Argentina) for Best Soundtrack \"El Mismo Amor, La Misma Lluvia\".\n* 1993 [[Premio Sur]] (Academy Award in Argentina) for Best Soundtrack \"A Place in the World\".\n* 1993 Silver Condor (Critics Award in Argentina) for Best Soundtrack \"A Place in the World\".\n\n<ref name=\":1\" /><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://filmmusicreporter.com/2014/04/07/ibero-american-film-industry-launches-platino-awards/|title=Ibero-American Film Industry Launches Platino Awards {{!}} Film Music Reporter|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-13}}</ref><ref name=\":3\" /><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://academiadecine.org.ar/premio-sur-2013/nominaciones/|title=Nominaciones|date=2014-06-01|website=Academia de Cine|language=es|access-date=2020-04-13}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://academiadecine.org.ar/premio-sur/premio-sur-2009/nominaciones/|title=Nominaciones|date=2014-10-02|website=Academia de Cine|language=es|access-date=2020-04-13}}</ref>\n\n==Filmography==\n*''Como Cortar a Tu Patan'' (2017) \u2013 Composer\n*''Numb, at the Edge of the End'' (2017) \u2013 Composer\n*''Day of Reckoning'' (2016) \u2013 Composer\n*''[[2091 (TV series)|2091]]'' (2016) \u2013 Composer\n*''[[Cumbia Ninja]]'' (2016) \u2013 Composer\n*''El Alien'' (2016) \u2013 Composer\n*''[[Secret in Their Eyes]]'' (2015) \u2013 Composer\n*''[[Underdogs (2013 animated film)|Underdogs]]'' (2015) \u2013 Composer\n*''Alice in Marialand'' (2014) \u2013 Composer\n*''Corazon de Leon'' (2013) \u2013 Composer\n*